Preheat your oven (for the ciabatta) to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Cut your @ciabatta{2} into 1cm thick slices.

On a lined #baking tray{}, toss with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and a pinch of @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Bake in the oven until crispy and golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes} (turn halfway through cooking for maximum crispiness).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Cut the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Roughly chop the @olives{1%sachet}.

Quarter the @lemon{1}.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g} (stalks and all).

Toss together the @salad leaves{40%g}, black beans, tomatoes, olives and parsley with the @balsamic glaze{2%sachets}, juice from half the lemon and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Season well to taste with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if required.

Divide the salad between #plates{}.

Arrange @smoked salmon{100%g}(thickly torn) and sliced ciabatta on top.

Serve remaining lemon wedges alongside for squeezing over.

> Black beans bring protein and fibre to the table in this simple and satisfying salad. The major flavour comes from thickly torn smoked salmon as well as bright and zesty lemon.